Rukshan Soza (born Christopher Rukshan Soza on 24 December 1966) was a Sri Lankan cricketer. He was a right-handed batsman who played for Berkshire. He was born in Colombo. Soza, who picked up three Youth Test and two Youth One Day International appearances for Sri Lanka Young Cricketers during a 1986 tour of England, made a single List A appearance for Berkshire, in the 1996 NatWest Trophy. From the opening order, Soza scored 10 runs, though Berkshire lost the match by a 106-run margin. 
